  "title": "Invocation for a family who invites you to break your fast with them",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 184",
  "arabic": "أَفْطَرَ عِنْدَكُمُ الصَّائِمُونَ وَأَكَلَ طَعَامَكُمُ الْأَبْرَارُ وَصَلَّتْ عَلَيْكُمُ الْمَلاَئِكَةُ",
  "meaning": "May the fasting break their fast in your home, and may the dutiful and pious eat your food, and may the angles send prayers upon you.",
